metadata.name: SPOT #158
metadata.description:
A study of circles, sizes, lines, colors, grains and alphas. The composition consists solely of 2d shapes but generates a 3d look. The base colors use a random chromaticity factor which results in a wild range of combinations. There is a 70% change on a dark background and 30% on a light background also 15% change on black and white. 

Press s in live mode for a 2000x2800 download

&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

metadata.name: Iteration is Usually Recursive (Pt. 1) #99
metadata.description:
This is the companion piece released with 'Iteration is Usually Recursive — Introduction: Finding answers in pre-computational art', the first in a series of essays, some long, some short, on generative art, theory and the practitioners of the medium. 

This piece started a simple experimen recreating George Nees’ Schotter (1968)— a classic piece of generative art history — as vanilla js SVG graphics. From there, I specifically developed it with non-plotter printing in mind, and more specific still, Riso Printing (think a scanner with a digital screen-printer MacGyver’d on). The palettes are taken from hex-estimated Risograph colour gamuts, with three layers being multiplied together to replicate, to some degree, the blending of the semi-transparent Risographic inks. Within this study, there’s a few different things going on, the initial setup is rectangles which cascade down the canvas, inheriting more extreme rotation as they get closer to the bottom (a la Schotter). The second is a subdivision of the shapes with filled circled, outlined circles and squares — since in this study the base shapes are rectangles and not squares, distribution of the ‘dithering’ can be larger than a single ‘pixel’ size — when these multiple layers overlap, the shapes produce a halftone-moire effect, forms and structures appear from the noise as the underlying patterns intersect. 

tx: Who?, Cosimo, Liam Egan, Andreas Rau, Louis

metadata.name: Desert Solitude #33
metadata.description: "Desert Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash) May 2022. 123 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Plantlets #69
metadata.description:
It all started with amazing work of Julien Leonard (https://twitter.com/julleor) and his blogposts explaining some of his explorations. 

All these prompted me to explore the basically a circle packing process combined with pattern replication in my own directions and style. I really liked the results and here I am with a project that is able to produce a wide variety of shapes from ivy plants spreading a cross a wall to city maps.

In this project the color palettes are produced algorithmically so please forgive me when some of them are not that pretty. :)


Keyboard shortcuts

- 1 : render @ 1024 x 1024 resolution
- 2 : render @ 2 x resolution
- 3 : render @ 3 x resolution
- 4 : render @ 4 x resolution
- c : show/hide the clipping layer 
- x : download canvas as PNG @ current resolution
